  <title>Gio.RemoteActionGroup::activate_action_full</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function vfunc_activate_action_full(action_name: String, parameter: <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link>, platform_data: <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link>): void {
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Activates the remote action.</p>  <p>This is the same as <link xref="Gio.ActionGroup.activate_action"/> except that it
allows for provision of "platform data" to be sent along with the
activation request.  This typically contains details such as the user
interaction timestamp or startup notification information.</p>  <p><code>platform_data</code> must be non-<code>null</code> and must have the type
%G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARDICT.  If it is floating, it will be consumed.</p>
  <p>Since 2.32</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>action_name</code></title>
  <p>the name of the action to activate</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>parameter</code></title>
  <p>the optional parameter to the activation</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>platform_data</code></title>
  <p>the platform data to send</p>
</item>
